        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23545",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ezameku",
                        "name": "ezameku",
                        "displayName": "Olivier Doucet",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "I made some additional tests.\n\nWhen the connection is OK, new mysqli() is returning a mysqli Object().\nWhen the error appears, the same object is returned, but cannot be used. Example :\n\nreal_escape_string() [function.mysqli-real-escape-string]: Couldn't fetch mysqli in Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Mysqli.php on line 114\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ezameku",
                        "name": "ezameku",
                        "displayName": "Olivier Doucet",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-20T06:15:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-20T06:15:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27619",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=belgattitude",
                        "name": "belgattitude",
                        "displayName": "S\u00e9bastien Vanvelthem",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\nI can confirm this issue at least on PHP 5.2.6 \/ Linux. As you said it happens only when the connection is not effective (failed because database not reachable, invalid login...). I don't agree with you on the fact that this is probably a PHP MySQLi related issue. \n\nThe problem is that when calling Zend_Db_Adapter_MySQLi::_connect(), we forget to unset the problematic mysqli object, let's see in ZF1.7.1 ::\n\n        if ($this->_connection === false || mysqli_connect_errno()) {\n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Mysqli\/Exception.php';\n            throw new Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli_Exception(mysqli_connect_error());\n        }\n\nPatched version \n\n        if ($this->_connection === false || mysqli_connect_errno()) {\n           \/\/ THE connection error was given with mysqli_connect_errno, the value of $this->_connection is a \"invalid\" mysqli object. So I reset it\n            $this->_connection = false; \n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Mysqli\/Exception.php';\n            throw new Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli_Exception(mysqli_connect_error());\n        }\n\nI'll post a separate bug report for this issue, hope this solution works \n\nThanks\n\nSeb\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=belgattitude",
                        "name": "belgattitude",
                        "displayName": "S\u00e9bastien Vanvelthem",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-23T06:19:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-23T06:19:56.000+0000"
                },
